          "datePublished": "2023-01-01",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My son is about to enter Grade 6 in RVS. Its been a long journey since he joined in Nursery almost 7 years back.  Hardworking, courteous and accessible Principal Ma'am, entire teaching staff, Admin staff, even the caring Didis and Guards, its a true Home away from home for the kids. Best part is that even after 6.5 hours in school, my kid is so reluctant to leave school even at 3 pm, as he enjoys playing in the Jhoola-Baari with his friends. For the past 2 years, my son is doing wonders in the game of chess, has won lots of trophies and medals, all due to the support of the school. Of course, academic content in the school is too good, they also keep updating of the Olympiads so that the kids can participate in them. Student-Teacher ratio is awesome, not like we have in Delhi schools, and many branded Gurugram schools, where they stuff 45-50 kids in each class. Blessed to be part of RVS family.\n\n- Vishal Jain (Happy parent)",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
